nd keep praying to Her. Intellectual comprehension falls flat beyond a point=\r\n. It is plain useless.=C3=82&nbsp;And the sadhana is not a one day/few mont=\r\nhs/one year or few years process. It is=C3=82&nbsp;like an endless ocean, t=\r\nhere are simply no limits except for the ones you set for yourself in your =\r\nown mind. One can experience the highest states of consciousness and yet no=\r\nt be able to comprehend the Chandi in totality. &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; -Regard=\r\ns&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp;Rajarshi&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Ami Jantra Tumi Jantri&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&gt; Ami Ghar Tumi Gharani&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Ami Ratha Tumi Rathi&lt;br&gt;\n&=\r\ngt; Jeman Chalao Temni Chali&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; _________________=\r\n_______________&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; From: priyank_priyank &lt;aks_day@...&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt;=\r\n To: &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; ymailto=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot; =\r\ntarget=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;mailto:vedic-wisdom%40yahoogroups.com&quot;&gt;vedic-wisd=\r\nom@yahoogroups.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Sent: Wednesday, 16 November 2011 8:09 AM&lt;b=\r\nr&gt;\n&gt; Subject: [vedic-wisdom] Why Sapthshati mantras is called Siddha man=\r\ntra?&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; =C3=82&nbsp; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Namaste all, &lt;br&gt;\n=\r\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; Its mentioned at many places over net that the mantra&#39;s in D=\r\nurga Saptshathi are siddha mantras. is there any particular reference for t=\r\nhis as to why they are called so?&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;a rel=3D&quot;nofollow&quot; ta=\r\nrget=3D&quot;_blank&quot; href=3D&quot;http://sanskritdocuments.org/all_pdf/saptashatIsidd=\r\nhasampuTamantra.pdf&quot;&gt;http://sanskritdocuments.org/all_pdf/saptashatIsiddhas=\r\nampuTamantra.pdf&lt;/a&gt;&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; will appreciate guidance in this re=\r\ngard&lt;br&gt;\n&gt; &lt;br&gt;\n&gt; t